oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of two American soldiers playing baseball
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This photograph shows two American soldiers posing with baseball equipment in their US Army uniforms. The soldier batting is undentified. The soldier catching is identified as Willie Lunn. However, the records do not reflect a soldier by that name. The catcher is either Berry Lunn or Willie Locke. Both men were from Williamson County, Tennessee. Lunn served in the 157th Depot Brig. and as a cook; Locke served in Btry. F, 114th FA, 30th Div.
